owl:Ontology.terms:description:
A taxonomy of building materials derived from the Getty Art & Architecture Thesaurus (Getty AAT: https://www.getty.edu/research/tools/vocabularies/aat/about.html), v2020-07-29.
Note: Contains information from the J. Paul Getty Trust, Getty Research Institute, the Art & Architecture Thesaurus, which is made available under the ODC Attribution License.
owl:Ontology.terms:title: AAT-buildingSITES taxonomy

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Aggregations of buildings, other structures, and/or open spaces, often multifunctional, and more extensive than single built works, usually shaped over a longer period of time by more participants.
Samenstellingen van gebouwen, andere bouwconstructies en open ruimten, vaak met meerdere functies; zijn uitgebreider en veelzijdiger dan afzonderlijk gebouwen.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: complex
complex (gebouw)
complexen
complexen (gebouwen)
complexes (buildings and sites)

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Complexen waar planten worden verbouwd of dieren gefokt voor levensonderhoud of handel.
Complexes where plants or animals are raised for livelihood or commerce.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: boerderij
boerderij (complex)
boerderijen
boerderijen (complexen)
farms
hoeven
hoeven (complexen)

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Boerenbedrijven die bestaan uit vele kleine boerderijtjes die zijn samengevoegd tot een eenheid waar gezamenlijk wordt gewerkt en die onder toezicht staan van de overheid of de provincie.
Farms consisting of many small holdings collected into a single unit for joint operation by a community under public or state supervision.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: collectief landbouwbedrijf
collectieve landbouwbedrijven
collective farms

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Farms chiefly devoted to the raising of dairy cattle and the production of milk, butter, and cheese.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: dairy farms
melkveebedrijf
melkveebedrijven

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Farms or areas of forest used to raise trees, typically managed in a way that ensures the regular production of trees to replace those extracted for timber or other purposes.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: boomkwekerij
boomkwekerij (landbouwcomplex)
boomkwekerijen
boomkwekerijen (landbouwcomplexen)
tree farms

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Farms that are considered historical because they preserve methods of rural life and farming from past centuries, whether for tourists, historical preservation, or to produce crops or livestock. For former farms that have been abandoned, use "abandoned farms."
owl:Class.rdfs:label: historic farms
historische boerderij
historische boerderijen
historische hoven

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Facilities where fish eggs are hatched and the fry raised, especially to stock lakes, streams, and ponds. Facilities where fish eggs are hatched and the fry raised, especially to stock lakes, streams, and ponds.
Inrichting waar visseneitjes worden uitgebroed en de jonge vissen, die later in meren, stromen en vijvers worden uitgezet, worden grootgebracht.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: fish hatcheries
viskwekerij
viskwekerijen

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Grote Spaans-Amerikaanse landgoederen, boerderijen of ranches; kan ook worden gebruikt voor het hoofdgebouw van een dergelijk complex.
Large Spanish landed estates common to 17th century Seville used as farms, or ranches. Also applies to Spanish-American estates and the main building of such a complex.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: haciendas
haciënda
haciënda's

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Grote, antieke Romeinse agrarische landgoederen.
Large, ancient Roman agricultural estates; for modern Spanish Latin American contexts, prefer "haciendas."
owl:Class.rdfs:label: latifundia
latifundia
latifundium

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Landed estates administered as units and consisting of the main residence (manor house), demesnes, and the land over which the lord has privileges.
Wordt gebruikt voor landgoederen die worden beheerd als een geheel en die bestaan uit een hoofdwoning (herenhuis), domeinen en het land waar de landheer privileges heeft.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: landgoed
landgoed (landbouwcomplex)
landgoederen
landgoederen (landbouwcomplexen)
manors (agricultural complexes)

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Generally, agricultural complexes usually worked by resident labor. More specifically, large estates in tropical or subtropical regions that are usually cultivated by resident unskilled or semi-skilled labor under central direction. Meaning and usage overlap with "estates(commercial agricultural holding)," although such estates are typically smaller enterprises than plantations.

In algemene zin, landbouwcomplexen die doorgaans worden bewerkt door ter plaatse gehuisveste arbeidskrachten. In meer specifieke zin verwijst de term naar grote landgoederen in tropische of subtropische gebieden die meestal worden bewerkt door ongeschoolde of laaggeschoolde arbeidskrachten, onder centraal toezicht.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: plantage
plantages
plantations

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Aanduiding voor vestigingen met veel grond die meestal worden gebruikt om koeien te laten grazen; groter dan boerderijen.
Denotes establishments with extensive landholdings usually for the grazing of cattle; larger than farms.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ranch
ranches
ranches (agricultural complexes)

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Ranches devoted primarily to the raising of beef cattle.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: cattle ranches
veefokkerij
veefokkerijen
vetweiderijen

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Ranches that provide entertainment for paying guests and tourists who wish to learn to ride horses or bulls, herd cattle, or do other activities associated with ranching.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: dude ranches
vakantieboerderij
vakantieboerderijen

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Tracts of land devoted to rearing sheep.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: schapenfokkerijen
schapenhouderij
schapenhouderijen
sheep farms

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Tracts of land on which grapevines are cultivated; plantations of vines.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: vineyards
wijngaard
wijngaarden

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Widened streets, neighborhood or town squares, or other mostly open public spaces where booths and stalls may be erected for public sales.
Wordt gebruikt voor verbrede straten, buurt- of stadspleinen of andere meestal openbare ruimten waar kraampjes en stalletjes kunnen worden opgebouwd voor verkoop.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: marketplaces
markt
markt (plein)
markten
markten (pleinen)
marktplaats
marktplaatsen

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Marketplaces, usually consisting of a network of covered streets, stalls, booths, and shops, common in parts of North Africa and West Asia.
Wordt gebruikt voor marktpleinen, meestal bestaande uit een netwerk van overdekte straten, stallen, kramen en winkels, veelvoorkomend in Noord-Afrika en West-Azië.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: bazaar
bazaar (marktplein)
bazaars
bazaars (marketplaces)
bazaars (marktpleinen)

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Buildings housing the offices, stages, backlots, sound stages, and other studios and operations of a motion picture studio company.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: filmstudio
filmstudio's
motion picture studios (building complexes)

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Aanduiding voor interneringscentra die worden opgericht los van het gangbare gevangenissysteem, waarin mensen worden opgesloten met het oog op de militaire of politieke veiligheid of voor bestraffing of exploitatie; mensen worden meestal gevangen gezet per decreet of op militair bevel, vaak ook hele klassen of groepen mensen, zonder rekening te houden met de schuldvraag van ieder individu afzonderlijk.

Designates internment centers established outside ordinary detention systems in which persons are confined for military or political security or for punishment or exploitation; persons are generally imprisoned by decree or military order, often including classes or groups of people without regard for their individual culpability.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: concentratiekamp
concentratiekampen
concentration camps

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Distant or overseas settlements established for punishing criminals by forced labour and isolation from society.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: penal colonies
strafkampen
strafkolonie
strafkolonies

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Minimum-security facilities where inmates work on, usually government-sponsored, forest, woods, or park conservation or maintenance projects.
Te gebruiken voor minimaal beveiligde strafinrichtingen waar de gestraften worden ingezet bij onderhoudsprojecten van bossen of parken, die meestal door de overheid worden gefinancierd.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: prison camps
werkkamp
werkkamp (gevangeniscomplex)
werkkampen
werkkampen (gevangeniscomplexen)

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Aanduiding voor de woning, het land en de eventuele bijgebouwen, waar een familie woont.
Designates the dwelling, land, and outbuildings, if any, where a family lives.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: homesteads
woonstede
woonsteden

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Refers to penal colonies where the prisoners are obliged to undertake heavy labor. Refers also to residential camps for migratory workers.
Verwijst naar strafinrichtingen waar de gedetineerden zware arbeid moeten verrichten. Verwijst tevens naar woonkampen voor gastarbeiders.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: labor camps
werkkamp
werkkampen

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Planned residential developments, generally publicly built and operated, intended for low- and moderate-income tenants.
Wordt gebruikt voor bouwprojecten, doorgaans in opdracht van de overheid gebouwd en beheerd, bedoeld voor huurders met lage inkomens.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: housing projects
huisvestingsproject
huisvestingsprojecten

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The dwellings or buildings of Fourierist communities. The dwellings or buildings of Fourierist communities.
Werkeenheden waarvan de leden in gemeenschap leven; uitgedacht door Fourier. VDE. De woningen of gebouwen van fourieristische gemeenschappen.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: falanstère
falanstères
phalansteries

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Distinguished from "trailer camps" by being only for infrequently moved prefabricated structures designed for year-round living.
Onderscheiden van 'caravanterreinen' doordat ze alleen gebruikt worden voor stacaravans.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: mobile home parks
stacaravanterrein
stacaravanterreinen

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Multistory, multiroom complex dwellings, often built on mesas or in cliffs, common among certain Indian cultures of the southwestern United States; distinguished from "Great Houses (complexes)" by their location and agglutinated construction.

Wordt gebruikt voor wooncomplexen met meerdere verdiepingen en meerdere vertrekken, vaak gebouwd op plateau's of in rotswanden, gangbaar bij bepaalde indiaanse culturen in het zuidwesten van de Verenigde Staten; te onderscheiden van 'Great Houses (complexen)' door hun ligging en samengeklonterde opbouw.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: pueblo
pueblo's
pueblos (housing complexes)

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Complexen van schoolgebouwen en andere faciliteiten; gebruik een specifiekere term waar mogelijk.
Groupings of educational buildings and other facilities; if possible, use a more specific term.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: educational complexes
onderwijscomplex
onderwijscomplexen

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: De bij universiteiten behorende terreinen (sportvelden enz.), ook de terreinen met gebouwen waar studenten (eventueel ook docenten) wonen.

Grounds of colleges or universities, including the open space between or around the buildings. The term is also used to refer to the grounds of other building complexes with layouts similar to colleges.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: campus
campuses
campussen

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Farms attached to education facilities either for the purpose of teaching agriculture or providing meats and produce to the parent institution. Farms attached to education facilities either for the purpose of teaching agriculture or providing meats and produce to the parent institution.
Wordt gebruikt voor boerderijen die verbonden zijn aan onderwijsinstellingen en waar les gegeven wordt in landbouw of die de school van levensmiddelen voorzien.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: school farms
schoolboerderij
schoolboerderijen

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Grounds and complexes designed to educate visitors about animals, plants, weather, and the environment, often including structures for educational activities and outdoor grounds containing native plant communities, wildlife habitats, walking trails, and other facilities.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: nature centers
natuurcentra
natuurcentrum

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Gardens, parks, or other grounds in which wild animals, and sometimes also domestic animals, are kept for public exhibition, usually in enclosures. Animals in zoos can generally be given more intensive care than is possible in nature reserves or wildlife refuges. Marine invertebrates, fish, and sometimes marine mammals, are often kept in separate aquariums.
Publieke tuinen waarin een verzameling (vreemde) dieren wordt onderhouden.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: dierentuin
dierentuinen
diergaarde
diergaarden
zoos (built complexes)

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Zoos designed for the education and enjoyment of children and young adults, often including a petting zoo, animal shows, and exhibits of baby animals.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: children's zoos
kinderdierentuin
kinderdierentuinen

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Plaatsen waar wilde of bijzondere dieren worden gehouden of vertoond.

Places where collections of wild or unusual animals are kept or exhibited in cages, particularly the early collections of emperors, kings, or other elite collectors, or 19th- and early 20th-century traveling exhibitions of caged animals. Traveling menageries were distinct from circuses in that the animals did not normally perform tricks.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: menagerie
menageries
menagerieën

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Zoos in which many or all of the animals have access to open-air enclosures that resemble the animals' natural habitats, in contrast to early zoos where most animals were confined to relatively small cages. Zoos in which many or all of the animals have access to open-air enclosures that resemble the animals' natural habitats, in contrast to early zoos where most animals were confined to relatively small cages.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: open-air zoos
openluchtdierentuin
openluchtdierentuinen

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Distinguished from "safari parks" by the complete and planned separation of the visiting public from the animals, who are allowed to roam freely within bounded natural habitats. Distinguished from "safari parks" by the complete and planned separation of the visiting public from the animals, who are allowed to roam freely within bounded natural habitats.
Te onderscheiden van 'safariparken' door de volledige en geplande afscheiding tussen bezoekers en dieren die vrij kunnen rondlopen binnen een begrensde natuurlijke omgeving.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: wild animal parks
wilde-dierenpark
wilde-dierenparken

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Algemene term voor ieder samenstel van verschillende soorten industriële gebouwen en aanverwante voorzieningen.
Use generally for any grouping of diversified industrial buildings and related facilities.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: industrial complexes
industrieel complex
industriële complexen

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Plaatsen of ruimten waar boten en schepen worden gebouwd of hersteld.
Places or enclosures where ships are built or repaired. For places servicing small vessels, use "boatyards." Places or enclosures where boats or ships are built or repaired.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: scheepswerf
scheepswerven
shipyards

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Groups of houses or tents and associated facilities designed as a residence for loggers who are temporarily in a forest to cut down and transport timber.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: houthakkerskamp
houthakkerskampen
lumber camps

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Refers to areas zoned and planned for so-called clean industries, developed and managed as a unit, where plots are offered fully equipped with transport and installation facilities, often already including a number of multi-use buildings.

Wordt gebruikt voor gebieden die zijn bestemd en gepland voor zogenaamde schone industrie, en die worden ontwikkeld en beheerd als een eenheid en waar percelen worden aangeboden met alle vervoers- en vestigingsvoorzieningen, doorgaans ook met een aantal multifunctionele gebouwen.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: industrial parks
industriepark
industrieparken

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Complexes of buildings and other structures with machinery for generating electricity. For individual buildings in which electricity, or other forms of power, are generated for the operation of machinery or vehicles, or supplying power to other buildings in a complex, use "powerhouses."
Wordt gebruikt voor complexen van gebouwen of andere bouwwerken met apparatuur voor het opwekken van elektriciteit.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: elektriciteitscentrales
elektrische centrales
energiecentrales
krachtcentrale
krachtcentrales
power plants

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Krachtcentrale waarin gas wordt verbrand met samengeperste lucht of olie, om stoom aangedreven turbines die elektrische energie produceren aan te drijven.
Power plants in which gas is burned, with compressed air or oil, to run steam-driven turbines that produce electrical energy.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: gas-turbine power plants
gasturbine-elektriciteitscentrales
gasturbinekrachtcentrale
gasturbinekrachtcentrales

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Elektriciteitscentrales waar elektriciteit wordt opgewekt met behulp van de energie van stromend water.
Power plants in which electricity is produced using the energy of flowing water.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: hydroelectric power plants
waterkrachtcentrale
waterkrachtcentrales

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Elektriciteitscentrales waarbij in periodes dat de vraag naar elektriciteit klein is, water naar grote hoogte wordt gepompt en daar wordt opgeslagen tot de vraag naar energie stijgt en dan wordt vrijgelaten waardoor hydraulische turbines worden aangedreven die de benodigde elektriciteit produceren.

Power plants using water pumped to and stored at a high elevation during periods of low energy demand, for use when demand is high, when water is released to operate hydraulic turbines to produce needed electricity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: pumped storage power plants
spaarbekkencentrale
spaarbekkencentrales

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Elektrische centrales die werken door middel van getijstroom.

Facilities designed to extract and store energy, employing one or more of the following methods, or other methods: harnessing energy from the differences between high tides and low tides by employing a "barrage" or type of dam to block receding water during ebb periods, the subsequent release of the water through a turbine generating electricity as the tide rises (similar to the workings of hydroelectric dams); using tidal stream power by utilizing ocean currents to drive turbines, particularly in areas around islands or coasts where these currents are fast, including systems that employ tidal fences where turbines are stretched across a channel or tidal turbines that resemble underwater wind turbines; using wave power systems to harness energy from the up-and-down motion of waves to drive energy production, installed in shoreline areas as well as offshore.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: getijcentrale
getijcentrales
tidal power plants

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Facilities that harness and distribute energy derived from the sun's radiation by producing heat, causing chemical reactions, or generating electricity in any of several methods, including but not limited to the following: by the using direct solar radiation to heat air, water, or another carrier fluid; by using arrays of lenses or mirrors as solar collectors to concentrate sunlight to produce high temperatures in a solar furnace; or by using solar cells (photovoltaic cells) to convert solar radiation into electricity when a small electric voltage is generated in the solar cell as light strikes the junction between a metal and a semiconductor (such as silicon) or the junction between two different semiconductors.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: solar power plants
zonne-energiecentrale
zonne-energiecentrales

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Elektriciteitscentrales die elektriciteit produceren door gebruik te maken van het temperatuurverschil tussen oppervlaktewater dat wordt verwarmd door de zon en koud water uit de diepte dat naar de oppervlakte wordt gepompt.

Power plants producing electricity by utilizing temperature differentials between surface water heated by the sun and deep cold water pumped to the surface. Power plants producing electricity by utilizing temperature differentials between surface water heated by the sun and deep cold water pumped to the surface.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ocean thermal energy conversion plant
ocean thermal energy conversion plants
ocean thermal energy conversion plants

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Gebruikt voor elektriciteitscentrales waarvan de voornaamste aandrijfmechanismen, voornamelijk turbines, verbonden met de generatoren worden aangedreven door stoom om de elektriciteit te genereren.
Power plants in which the prime movers, usually turbines, connected to the generators are driven by steam to produce electricity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: steam power plants
stoom-elektriciteitscentrales
stoomkrachtcentrale
stoomkrachtcentrales

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Elektriciteitscentrales op stoom, waarbij kolen als voornaamste brandstof wordt gebruikt.
Steam-producing, electric power generating plants using coal as the primary fuel.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: coal-fired power plants
kolengestookte centrale
kolengestookte centrales

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Elektriciteitscentrales die op stoom uit geothermale bronnen werken, bijvoorbeeld geisers, heetwaterbronnen of vulkanen. LEH.
Power plants using steam generated by geothermal sources, such as geysers, hot springs, or volcanoes.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: geothermal power plants
geothermische centrale
geothermische centrales

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Facilities that create and distribute power obtained from nuclear reactors, which initiate and control a self-sustaining series of nuclear fissions.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: atoomcentrale
atoomcentrales
kerncentrales
kernenergiecentrales
nucleaire centrale
nucleaire centrales
nuclear power plants

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Large scale energy conversion centers that burn the fossil fuel oil to produce electricity. Large scale energy conversion centers that burn the fossil fuel oil to produce electricity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: oil-fired power plants
oliegestookte elektriciteitscentrales
oliegestookte krachtcentrale
oliegestookte krachtcentrales

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Facilities designed for the creation and distribution of power derived from wind, where turbines convert the kinetic energy of wind into mechanical or electrical energy that can be used for power.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: wind power plants
windkrachtcentrale
windkrachtcentrales

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Use only for military weapons testing; for small arms target ranges, use "shooting ranges" or a more specific term.
Wordt alleen gebruikt voor het uittesten van militaire wapens; gebruik 'schietterreinen' of een specifiekere term voor oefenterreinen voor kleine vuurwapens.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: firing ranges
testgebied
testgebieden

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Use generally in contemporary contexts for permanent centers of operations; use "military camps" for contemporary nonpermanent posts.
Wordt tegenwoordig doorgaans gebruikt voor permanente militaire bases; gebruik 'kampementen' voor tijdelijke posten.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: militaire bases
militaire basis
military bases

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Bases for the operation of military aircraft.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: air bases
luchtmachtbases
luchtmachtbasis

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Land-based military airbases for the military aviation division of the navy of a nation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: marineluchtvaartbases
marineluchtvaartbasis
naval air bases

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Een permanente militaire bases waar een plaatselijke commandant de leiding heeft, die bestaat uit ondersteunende faciliteiten die nodig zijn bij legeractiviteiten, inclusief beveiliging, interne communicatie en nutssystemen.

Permanent group of installations for which a local commander is responsible, consisting of support facilities necessary for army activities, including security, internal communications, and utility systems.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: army bases
legerbases
legerbasis

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Military bases for the storage and deployment of guided missiles, which are self-propelled projectiles used as weapons, including but not limited to long-range ballistic missiles.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: guided missile bases
raketbases
raketbases (geleide raketten)
raketbasis
raketbasis (geleide raketten)

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Facilities specializing in the training of military personnel, typically including training in the use of weapons, discipline, endurance, and survival training.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: militair trainingskamp
militaire opleidingskampen
militaire trainingskampen
military training camps

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Area naval commands normally including a seaport, which integrates shore activities that provide local logistic services to the fleet.
Marinebasis, meestal met een zeehaven, waar aan wal de plaatselijke logistieke diensten voor de vloot worden verzorgd.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: marinebases
marinebasis
naval bases

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Marinebases waar oorlogsschepen worden gebouwd, hersteld, gedokt of omgebouwd door civiele ingenieurs en arbeiders en die worden beheerd door genie-officieren.
Naval bases that build, repair, dock, or convert warships, and are manned by civilian engineers and workers and administered by engineer duty officers.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: marinewerf
marinewerven
naval shipyards

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Military bases that shelter and deploy submarines and personnel.
Plaatsen, havens waar duikboten gestationeerd zijn, vanwaaruit zij varen.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: duikbootbases
duikbootbasis
submarine bases

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: In contemporary military contexts this refers to groups of huts, tents, or other shelters set up temporarily for troops. In historical contexts the term connotes permanent or semipermanent places of encampment. Use "military bases" for contemporary permanent installations. In contemporary military contexts this refers to groups of huts, tents, or other shelters set up temporarily for troops. In historical contexts the term connotes permanent or semipermanent places of encampment. Use "military bases" for contemporary permanent installations.

Wordt in hedendaags militair verband gebruikt voor groepen hutten, tenten of ander tijdelijk onderdak voor troepen; wordt in historische context gebruikt voor permanenete of semipermanente kampplaatsen; gebruik 'militaire bases' voor hedendaagse permanente legerplaatsen.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: militair kamp
militaire kampen
military camps

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Multifunctional Islamic fortified outposts generally reserved for warriors of the Faith who are committed to defense of frontiers and to proselytizing. Multifunctional Islamic fortified outposts generally reserved for warriors of the Faith who are committed to defense of frontiers and to proselytizing.

Wordt gebruikt voor multifunctionele, islamitische versterkte buitenposten die meestal zijn alleen zijn bestemd voor strijders voor het Geloof, die zich toeleggen op de verdediging van grenzen en het bekeren van mensen.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ribat
ribats
ribats

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Target range for guided missiles.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: guided missile ranges
testgebied voor geleide projectielen
testgebieden voor geleide projectielen

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Building complexes that house offices and facilities for the support of the offices.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: kantoorcomplex
kantoorcomplexen
office complexes

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Areas of land or property where many office buildings may be grouped together and developed specifically to attract corporate offices.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: kantoorpark
kantoorparken
office parks

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Commercially developed real estate tracts commonly consisting of one- to four-unit dwellings.
Wordt gebruikt voor commerciëel ontwikkelde onroerend-goedgebieden die meestal bestaan uit één- tot vier-kamer woningen.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: housing developments
nieuwbouwproject
nieuwbouwprojecten
